<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 2; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes; height: 369.75pt;">
<td style="width: 451.25pt; border: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; border-top: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; padding: 6.0pt 6.0pt 6.0pt 6.0pt; height: 369.75pt;" width="602">
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">Name: Jessica Brown</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">Tel: 5823 2210</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">Under warranty: yes</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">Model type: a {top}</span><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;"> mount</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">Model number: S 654 391 X</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">Colour: {silver}</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">Date of purchase: {12th January|12 Janurary}</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif;"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: Gungsuh; color: #15191e;">Problems: ∙ the {alarm} </span></span><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">in the fridge sounded</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif;"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: Gungsuh; color: #15191e;">∙ freezer temperature is <strong>{10} </strong></span></span><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">degrees</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif;"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: Gungsuh; color: #15191e;">∙ main fridge not working.</span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">Nearest service centre: Ken’s Appliances (near the <strong>{station}</strong></span><strong><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">)</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><u><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">Comments</span></u><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;">:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif;"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: Gungsuh; color: #15191e;">∙ customer needs the fridge to store food for her <strong>{sandwich}</strong></span></span><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;"> shop</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif;"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: Gungsuh; color: #15191e;">∙ value of food in fridge</span><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: Gungsuh; color: #15191e; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"> <strong>{180}</strong></span><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: Gungsuh; color: #15191e;">: $ 8</span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif;"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: Gungsuh; color: #15191e;">To do: ∙ get the <strong>{manager}</strong></span></span><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e;"> to call her today</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="vi" style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif;"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: Gungsuh; color: #15191e;">∙ replace damaged <strong>{door}</strong></span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Question 1-10</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>SERVICE REP (Ian):</strong> Hello, Superior Home Appliances, this is Ian here.</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER (Jessica Brown):</strong> Oh, hello. Yes, I have a new fridge, and I’m ringing to report a fault with it. I need you to send someone out to have a look at it.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> OK, I’ll fill in a customer complaint form and arrange for one of our repair agents to come out to you.</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> OK then.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> Now, can I just get some contact details from you for the form? Your name is—</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Jessica—<strong>Jessica Brown</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> Okay. And if I can just get a contact telephone number—</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Our home phone number is <strong>5 8 2 3 2 2 1 0</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> Got it. Now, can I get some more details about the fridge?</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Well, it’s been playing up since yesterday afternoon.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> I see, and is it still under warranty?</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Well, I should think so—it’s only a couple of weeks old.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> That’s fine then. Now I just need to get some more information about the make and model. Is it a top mount, a bottom mount, or a side-by-side?</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> (Question 1) The freezer is on <strong>top</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> And have you got the model number there?</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Yes, it’s here on the instructions booklet—it’s <strong>S654391X</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> OK. (Question 2) So it’s <strong>silver</strong> in colour?</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> That’s right. I thought it was so much nicer than the usual white ones.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> Now, if I could just get a few details from you. First, when did you buy the fridge?</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Well, as I said, it was only a few weeks ago, but I don’t have the receipt in front of me at the moment. I do know that it was delivered on the 6th of February.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> OK, well, I can use that date to search on the computer… um… hmm… ah, here it is. (Question 3) It says here you bought it on <strong>January the 12th</strong>.</p>\n<hr />\n<h3>2. Mô tả Lỗi và Bồi thường</h3>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> Now, what exactly is wrong with the fridge?</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> (Question 4) My fridge is fitted with an <strong>alarm</strong>, and it started to go off—it made an awful noise.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> So what was wrong?</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Well, when I went to check the freezer, it felt pretty warm. (Question 5) It’s <strong>10 degrees</strong> and it should be minus 18, so everything is melting. And then the main part of the fridge doesn’t seem to be working either.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> Hmm, I see.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> I’ve made a note of that on the form, and I’ll pass it on to the service agent.</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> When can they come and fix it?</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> Let’s find the closest one to you… um, let’s see… that’s Ken’s Appliances, and they’ve got two centres in your area—one near the station and another one in the shopping centre.</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Well, we’re miles away from the shopping centre, so (Question 6) the <strong>station</strong> one would be closer.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> I’ll ring them in a minute, but I should warn you, it could take a day or two for them to get to you.</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> What? What am I going to do without a fridge? Look, there’s a fridge full of food there and it’s all going off—I’ll have to throw it all out, you know.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> Yes, I do sympathise.</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> It’s not just that—this is going to affect my business. (Question 7) I run a <strong>sandwich shop</strong> and that’s where I keep my stock.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> I see. Look, Jessica, if you tell me how much the stock is worth, we can send you a cheque for that amount—though there is a maximum of $250.</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Well, (Question 8) I’ve just filled it with <strong>$180</strong> worth of meat and salad, so that would be something, I suppose. But how long is my business expected to survive without a fridge? It’s just not good enough.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> Yes, I understand your concerns, but that’s all I can really offer you.</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Well, I’d like to speak to someone higher up about this.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> Um, (Question 9) I can ask my <strong>manager</strong> to ring you back by <strong>close of business today</strong>—would that be acceptable?</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Yes, thank you.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> I do apologise for all the inconvenience. Is there anything else I can help you with?</p>\n<p><strong>CUSTOMER:</strong> Actually there is one more thing—(Question 10) the door has a <strong>dent</strong> in it on the <strong>left-hand side</strong>. It wasn’t there in the shop, so it must have happened when it was delivered. I’d like that replaced too.</p>\n<p><strong>REP:</strong> I’ll make a note of that too. You’ll be hearing from us very soon.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('17bf39e7-8a41-4b93-a2c1-63360656ba3c', 'fbc00326-5efd-44b1-aa0c-61d7fffa258e', 'fillup', 'Question 31-40', '<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Monarch Butterflies</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Hibernation</strong></p>
<p>– Butterfly species adopt different hibernation patterns during their life cycle. Butterflies named ‘Banded Hair Freak’ hibernate in the form of an {egg}.<br />
– A species called ‘Dapple White’ accumulates {energy} from the larval stage.<br />
– Slow metabolism can help them to sort out some problems in winter. A substance is produced in the blood which may function as {anti-freeze}.<br />
– There are few predators because they can only survive in {warm} weather.</p>
<p><strong>Migration</strong></p>
<p>– Monarch butterflies move to {North America} in winter. To avoid cold temperature, they migrate to the south in large groups.<br />
– The survival skill can help them last for up to {6 months} during a long journey.<br />
– Monarch butterflies fly in the daytime and stay in {trees} during the night.<br />
– Researchers found out that they orient by flying along the {rivers}. They also follow the direction of the {sun} for navigational aid.<br />
– During migration, they mainly feed on flowers and cannot reproduce. Recently the annual arrival of the monarchs can be a good interest to {tourists} in the region.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 4</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student:</strong> <span class=\"citation-739 citation-740 citation-741 citation-742 citation-end-742\">We were required to do the investigation regarding survival strategies of particular animals, and I chose to study how the butterflies will do for survival when cold weather and food shortage could easily influence their life cyc</span><span class=\"citation-739 citation-740 citation-741 citation-end-741\">le. I concentrated on a number of main strategie</span><span class=\"citation-739 citation-740 citation-end-740\">s butterflies adopt to handle these harsh conditi</span><span class=\"citation-739 citation-end-739\">ons: hibernation and migration.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><span class=\"citation-738 citation-end-738\">First, let’s talk about the hibernation, which means a long-term sleep in which an animal’s metabolism slows to conserve strengt</span><span class=\"\">h.</span><span class=\"\"> Various butterfly species have formed different patterns of hibernation at continuous periods of their life cycle.</span><span class=\"\"> For example,</span><span class=\"\"> the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"263\">Banded Hair Streak</strong><span class=\"\"> hardly hibernates in its full-grown adult form,</span><span class=\"\"> but as an </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"340\">(31) egg</strong><span class=\"\">.</span></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><span class=\"\">And another species,</span><span class=\"\"> the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">Dappled White</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> breathes during the winter in a crystallized stage,</span><span class=\"\"> and during this time,</span><span class=\"\"> it’s able to draw on the </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">(32) <span class=\"citation-737\">energy</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-737 citation-end-737\"> it stimulated earlier on in its larval stage.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-736\">Though the slowing of the metabolism in hibernation functions with many of the difficulties faced in winter, it can’t prevent them all. In addition, some butterflies have extra plans for survival. For instance, they develop a substance in their blood, usually in glycerol or sorbitol, which serves as </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"301\"><span class=\"citation-736 citation-end-736\">(</span>33) antifreeze</strong><span class=\"\"> (hoặc </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"323\">anti-freeze</strong><span class=\"\">),</span></span><span class=\"\"> thereby adding extra resistance against lower temperatures.</span><span class=\"\"> Actually,</span><span class=\"\"> there is a positive side to the cold weather:</span><span class=\"\"> fewer predators exist to cause problems.</span><span class=\"\"> This is because they’re mainly active in </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"535\">(34) warm</strong></span><span class=\"\"> weather.</span></p>\n<hr class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7\" />\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student:</strong> <span class=\"citation-735\">So now let’s move on to the second type of survival strategy the butterflies used in winter: migration. That means moving to regions with a more suitable </span><span class=\"citation-733 citation-734 citation-735 citation-end-735\">environment. I’m going to start this topic with a detailed study about particular cases of migratory species: the</span><span class=\"citation-733 citation-734 citation-end-734\"> Monarch butterfly.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><span class=\"citation-731 citation-732 citation-end-732\">Many butterfly species found in various zones of the world migrate, like</span><span class=\"citation-731 citation-end-731\"> the Red Admiral, a British butterfly which winters in North Afri</span><span class=\"\">ca.</span><span class=\"\"> But the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">Monarch</strong><span class=\"\"> butterfly is the sole example to do this in </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"201\">(35) North America</strong></span><span class=\"\"> at any stage of the life cycle.</span><span class=\"\"> The </span><span class=\"citation-729 citation-730 citation-end-730\">Monarch cannot survive in the low winter temperatures, so when it gets cold, the Monarchs begin to gather in huge groups and fly south. They can travel up to three and a half thousand miles.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><span class=\"citation-727 citation-728 citation-end-728\">But only the last summer generation of Monarchs migrate. Norm</span><span class=\"citation-727 citation-end-727\">al generations only live for a maximum of 10 days; in fact, the last migration generation, as reported</span><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> lives for </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"175\">(36) six months</strong><span class=\"\"> (hoặc </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">6 months</strong><span class=\"\">),</span></span><span class=\"\"> which enables them to take such a long journey.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><span class=\"\">These huge teams of migrating Monarchs only fly during daylight hours,</span><span class=\"\"> and at night they usually have a rest in </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">(37) trees</strong><span class=\"\">,</span></span><span class=\"\"> again often in vast groups.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><span class=\"\">Research is now being done into what encourages them to reach the destination.</span> It has been known for years that they find their way on the journey by following<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">(38) rivers</strong></span></span>, and there are a few of these along the migratory route. However, the new research indicates that they may also treat the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"294\">(39) sun</strong></span> as a navigational aid.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><span class=\"\">During this time they are able to feed,</span><span class=\"\"> mainly from a type of flower called milkweed,</span> but they are not able to reproduce during this period.<span class=\"\"> The Monarchs land in their lineage to a particular region in Mexico known as the Sierra Chincua.</span><span class=\"\"> The Monarchs are anticipated with great interest within the region,</span><span class=\"\"> and over recent years,</span><span class=\"\"> their annual arrival has gained great popularity among </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"384\">(40) tourists</strong></span><span class=\"\">.</span> However, their habitat has been increasingly threatened.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9e1f86e6-0081-427e-b855-0807948ce081', '06af1a69-1a4b-4d54-a58f-91cc45328f06', 'fillup', 'Questions 33 – 35', '<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="53">NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer. </p>
<ul data-path-to-node="14">
<li>
<p>How many Western classical composers are identified as exceptionally talented?{16| 16 individuals}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Which composer initially received little recognition for his work?{Sebastian Bach| Bach}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Who can help improve the performance of people practising daily?{coaches }</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. How many Western classical composers are identified as exceptionally talented? — {16 / 16 individuals}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…in music, <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">16 individuals</strong> have produced about 50 per cent of the Western classical music…” (Đoạn B).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Which composer initially received little recognition for his work? — {Bach / Sebastian Bach}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “It should surprise no-one that for <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">Bach</strong> to be considered a great musician, standards of music <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">needed to change</strong> to embrace the qualities that his compositions possessed.” (Đoạn C).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Điều này ngụ ý ban đầu ông chưa được coi là vĩ đại cho đến khi tiêu chuẩn âm nhạc thay đổi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Who can help improve the performance of people practising daily? — {coaches}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…with the assistance of their <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">coaches</strong>, have access to the best techniques.” (Đoạn E).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('aeaf44f7-ec88-4c23-bae4-4b6bbdd1599a', '36bb5599-0fa1-4eed-b781-3a5b7b904f4b', 'radio', 'Questions 27–30', NULL, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Choose<strong> YES i</strong>f the statement agrees with the claims of the writer <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</span></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The conflicting nature of mirrors makes them inappropriate aids for investigating human thought."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Humans find it difficult to distinguish between reflections of two- and three-dimensional objects."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Illusions using mirrors can help in the treatment of medical problems."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Mirrors for use in scientific experiments have to be constructed to precise specifications."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>27. NO<br />(Đoạn 2: “&#8230;mirrors make them effective and accessible tools for exploring questions about perception and cognition in humans&#8230;”)<br />→ Mặc dù gương có bản chất “phức tạp và đơn giản đồng thời”, chúng vẫn được xem là công cụ hiệu quả để nghiên cứu nhận thức và tư duy con người, chứ không “không phù hợp”.<br />→ Đáp án: NO</p>\n<p> <br />28. NOT GIVEN<br />→ Bài có nói gương giúp con người nghiên cứu nhận thức và cách não tái tạo hình ảnh 3D, nhưng không nói rằng con người gặp khó khăn khi phân biệt vật phản chiếu 2D và vật thật 3D.<br />→ Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</p>\n<p> <br />29. YES<br />(Đoạn 2: “Mirrors are applied in medicine&#8230; trick the brain into healing itself. Mirror therapy has been successful in treating chronic pain and paralysis.”)<br />→ Liệu pháp sử dụng gương đã giúp điều trị thành công đau mãn tính và liệt, chứng minh rằng ảo ảnh qua gương có thể hỗ trợ y học.<br />→ Đáp án: YES</p>\n<p> <br />30. NOT GIVEN<br />→ Đoạn văn không đề cập đến việc gương dùng trong thí nghiệm khoa học phải được chế tạo theo tiêu chuẩn chính xác, chỉ nói chung về việc gương được dùng trong nghiên cứu và y học.<br />→ Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('69ec88a8-4cc8-43dc-b0f0-ec3eee01c087', '36bb5599-0fa1-4eed-b781-3a5b7b904f4b', 'radio', 'Questions 31–34', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B, C or D.<br />Write the correct letter in boxes 31–34 on your answer sheet.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. monitor the behaviour of other subjects. "}, {"content": "B. act more industriously and independently. "}, {"content": "C. become less confident of themselves. "}, {"content": "D. focus overwhelmingly on their own reflection."}], "question": "If a mirror is present during certain experiments, the subjects tend to "}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. more tolerant of others. "}, {"content": "B. more satisfied with their own lives. "}, {"content": "C. more open to learning from others. "}, {"content": "D. more likely to accept unpopular ideas."}], "question": "Research results imply that physical self-reflection leads people to be "}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. find the image in the mirror uninteresting. "}, {"content": "B. recognise the basic need for personal cleanliness. "}, {"content": "C. realise that the marks they see are on their own body. "}, {"content": "D. understand that marks on their face have been made deliberately."}], "question": "The successful completion of a well-known mirror test suggests that the animal subjects "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. Conflicting interpretations of mirror research "}, {"content": "B. Psychological responses to mirror images "}, {"content": "C. The physical properties of mirrors "}, {"content": "D. The use of mirrors through history"}], "question": "Which of the following is the most suitable title for Reading Passage 3? "}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>31. B. act more industriously and independently.<br />(Đoạn 3: “Subjects tested in a room with a mirror have been found to work harder and to be less inclined to cheat&#8230;”)<br />→ Khi có gương trong phòng, người tham gia làm việc chăm chỉ hơn và ít gian lận hơn, nghĩa là họ hành động độc lập và có ý thức hơn → Đáp án: B. act more industriously and independently.</p>\n<p> <br />32. A. more tolerant of others.<br />(Đoạn 3: “People in a room with a mirror were comparatively less likely to make judgements about others based on negative social stereotypes concerning, for example, sex, race or religion.”)<br />→ Khi có gương, người tham gia ít phán xét người khác dựa trên định kiến tiêu cực, cho thấy họ khoan dung hơn với người khác → Đáp án: A. more tolerant of others.</p>\n<p> <br />33. C. realise that the marks they see are on their own body.<br />(Đoạn 4: “&#8230;have passed the famed mirror self-recognition test, which means they will&#8230; scrutinize marks that have been applied to their faces or bodies.”)<br />→ Những con vật vượt qua bài kiểm tra nhận thức qua gương nhận ra các dấu vết trên cơ thể mình, nghĩa là chúng hiểu hình ảnh trong gương chính là bản thân → Đáp án: C. realise that the marks they see are on their own body.</p>\n<p> <br />34. B. Psychological responses to mirror images.<br />→ Bài đọc tập trung vào việc con người và động vật phản ứng tâm lý như thế nào với hình ảnh trong gương – từ nghiên cứu nhận thức, tự nhận thức, cho tới hành vi xã hội.<br />→ Các lựa chọn khác (về vật lý hoặc lịch sử của gương) chỉ là phụ, không phải trọng tâm → Đáp án: B. Psychological responses to mirror images.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('55a7731f-5557-4706-a4fd-cab883285d18', '36bb5599-0fa1-4eed-b781-3a5b7b904f4b', 'matrix', 'Questions 35 – 40', NULL, '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, A–I, below.<br />Choose the correct letter, A–I, in boxes 35–40 on your answer sheet.</p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Dr Epley found that when identifying images of themselves, people", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "When trying to identify images of unfamiliar individuals, Dr Epley found that people most frequently", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Dr Epley says that a single objective reflection is impossible because people", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Dr Epley says that when forming an opinion of how they think they look, people", "correctCategoryLetter": "I"}, {"itemText": "When guessing the size of their mirrored face from close up, people", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "As they imagine stepping backwards from a mirror, people", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "believe they can improve their looks by being friendly.", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "are confronted daily with their images in a variety of situations.", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "assume their image will get progressively smaller.", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "recognise familiar faces much more readily.", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "estimate the image to be larger than it actually is.", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "select those photographs which have not been altered.", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "find there is little change in the image they face.", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "locate the photographs faster if they are made to look attractive.", "categoryLetter": "H"}, {"categoryText": "create a positive generalised self image.", "categoryLetter": "I"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>35. H – locate the photographs faster if they are made to look attractive.<br />(Đoạn: “Participants identified their personal photographs significantly quicker when their faces had been computer-enhanced to be more appealing&#8230;”)<br />→ Khi ảnh được chỉnh sửa cho đẹp hơn, người tham gia nhận ra ảnh của mình nhanh hơn → đáp án H.</p>\n<p> <br />36. F – select those photographs which have not been altered.<br />(Đoạn: “When asked to match photographs of strangers, participants were&#8230; best at spotting unenhanced faces.”)<br />→ Khi nhận diện khuôn mặt người lạ, họ nhận ra nhanh hơn các ảnh chưa chỉnh sửa → đáp án F.</p>\n<p> <br />37. B – are confronted daily with their images in a variety of situations.<br />(Đoạn: “Although we do indeed see ourselves in the mirror every day, we don’t look exactly the same every time&#8230;”)<br />→ Tiến sĩ Epley nói rằng con người nhìn thấy bản thân trong nhiều tình huống khác nhau mỗi ngày, nên không có hình ảnh phản chiếu “khách quan duy nhất” → đáp án B.</p>\n<p> <br />38. I – create a positive generalised self image.<br />(Đoạn: “They piece together a mental representation formed from different aspects of themselves when they are looking their best.”)<br />→ Khi đánh giá ngoại hình, con người tạo ra hình ảnh tổng hợp tích cực nhất về bản thân → đáp án I.</p>\n<p> <br />39. E – estimate the image to be larger than it actually is.<br />(Đoạn: “People overwhelmingly say ‘The outline of my face on the mirror would be pretty much the size of my face.’ &#8230; Both answers, it turns out, are wrong.”)<br />→ Họ ước lượng kích thước khuôn mặt trong gương lớn hơn thực tế, vì thật ra nó chỉ bằng một nửa kích thước thật → đáp án E.</p>\n<p> <br />40. C – assume their image will get progressively smaller.<br />(Đoạn: “As for the second question&#8230; if I move away from the mirror, the size of my image will shrink with each step.”)<br />→ Mọi người cho rằng hình ảnh trong gương sẽ nhỏ dần khi họ lùi lại, dù thực tế không phải vậy → đáp án C.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('13e6fdd1-ac9b-447c-b79e-1e260727af11', '3153cf39-3063-4779-8f50-99f72bffc690', 'fillup', 'Questions 23–26', '<p>Complete the sentences. Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>In the 18th century, people could show their superiority by understanding when either {silence} or applause was appropriate.</p>
<p>Performers in the 18th century, in particular those singing in the {opera}, no longer had a meaningful dialogue with their audiences.</p>
<p>In the 19th century, applause was no longer offered as a {reward} to performers.</p>
<p>Nowadays our expressions of approval are seen as {permanent} in comparison to the applause of the past.</p>', '<p dir="ltr">Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p dir="ltr">Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>H</strong>, in boxes 21-26.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. silence</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 6, dòng 3–5.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Knowing when to maintain <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">silence</strong>, as well as when to clap, became a mark of sophistication, a kind of code for audiences to learn.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong thế kỷ 18, việc hiểu rõ các quy tắc ứng xử — cụ thể là biết lúc nào nên giữ sự im lặng và lúc nào nên vỗ tay — được xem là minh chứng cho sự tinh tế và vị thế của khán giả. Cụm “show their superiority” trong câu hỏi tương ứng với “mark of sophistication” trong bài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. opera</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 6, dòng 6–8.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Applause became much less of a true dialogue with an audience, especially so with <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">opera</strong>, where the singers saw it as part of a basic transaction with the crowd.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả nhấn mạnh rằng sự tương tác thực sự giữa nghệ sĩ và khán giả đã giảm dần, đặc biệt là trong loại hình nhạc kịch (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">opera</strong>). Ở đó, các ca sĩ coi tiếng vỗ tay chỉ là một phần của sự trao đổi cơ bản thay vì là một cuộc đối thoại tinh thần.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. reward</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 6, câu cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…applause had become standardized and institutionalized, and had become an expectation rather than the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">reward</strong> it used to be.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bước sang thế kỷ 19, tiếng vỗ tay đã trở thành một quy chuẩn và là điều mặc định phải có. Nó không còn mang ý nghĩa là một phần thưởng dành cho sự nỗ lực hay tài năng của nghệ sĩ như trong quá khứ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. permanent</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 7, câu cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…our kind of applause matters more now, in many ways, because it is no longer momentary and short-lived, but is far more <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">permanent</strong> instead.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong thời đại kỹ thuật số, các hình thức tán thưởng trực tuyến được coi là có sức nặng hơn vì chúng mang tính lâu dài và vĩnh viễn. Điều này đối lập hoàn toàn với tiếng vỗ tay truyền thống vốn chỉ vang lên nhất thời rồi biến mất.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"> </p>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b4e6008a-48f0-40c3-887d-508bbb157113', '9e74c3bb-ed43-4df5-bbd1-f548be9e70f2', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Andrew Parker failed to make effective water device which can be used in desert."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Skin of lizard is easy to get wet when it contacts water."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Scientists apply inspiration from nature into many artificial engineering."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Tiny and thin hair under gecko’s feet allows it to stick to the surface of object."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "When gecko climbs downward, its feet release a certain kind of chemical to make them adhesive."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Famous cases stimulate a large number of successful products of biomimetics in real life."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Velcro is well-known for its bionics design."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1. NOT GIVEN<br />(Đoạn A: “Parker had come here to discover precisely how it does this&#8230; to make a thorny-devil-inspired device that will help people collect lifesaving water in the desert.”)<br />→ Đoạn văn chỉ nói Parker đang nghiên cứu để tạo ra thiết bị lấy nước, không nhắc đến việc ông thất bại hay thành công.<br />→ Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</p>\n<p> <br />2. FALSE<br />(Đoạn A: “Its skin is far more hydrophobic than I thought.”)<br />→ Da thằn lằn rất kỵ nước, nghĩa là không dễ bị ướt khi tiếp xúc với nước.<br />→ Đáp án: FALSE</p>\n<p> <br />3. TRUE<br />(Đoạn B: “Parker’s work is only a small part of an increasingly vigorous, global biomimetics movement. Engineers in Bath&#8230; architects in Zimbabwe&#8230; Japanese medical researchers&#8230;” )<br />→ Nhiều nhà khoa học ứng dụng cảm hứng từ tự nhiên vào kỹ thuật và y học hiện đại.<br />→ Đáp án: TRUE</p>\n<p> <br />4. TRUE<br />(Đoạn E: “&#8230;owe their remarkable adhesion to some two billion spatula-tipped filaments&#8230; each filament only a hundred nanometers thick&#8230; they interact at the molecular level with the surface.”)<br />→ Khả năng bám dính của thằn lằn đến từ các sợi lông siêu nhỏ dưới bàn chân, giúp chúng bám vào bề mặt vật thể.<br />→ Đáp án: TRUE</p>\n<p> <br />5. NOT GIVEN<br />→ Không có thông tin nói rằng thằn lằn tiết ra hóa chất khi leo xuống. Đoạn E chỉ nhắc đến lực van der Waals, chứ không có chất dính hay hóa học nào được tiết ra.<br />→ Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</p>\n<p> <br />6. FALSE<br />(Đoạn H: “&#8230;bio-inspiration has led to surprisingly few mass-produced products and arguably only one household word – Velcro&#8230;”)<br />→ Dù có nhiều nghiên cứu nổi tiếng, nhưng sản phẩm ứng dụng thực tế rất ít, không có “large number of successful products”.<br />→ Đáp án: FALSE</p>\n<p> <br />7. TRUE<br />(Đoạn H: “&#8230;Velcro, which was invented in 1948 by Swiss chemist George de Mestral, by copying the way cockleburs clung to his dog’s coat.”)<br />→ Velcro là một sản phẩm nổi tiếng được thiết kế dựa trên nguyên lý sinh học tự nhiên (bionic design).<br />→ Đáp án: TRUE</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b4929d5d-a2f4-4f69-8045-4994d2a5645c', '9e74c3bb-ed43-4df5-bbd1-f548be9e70f2', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–10', '<p data-start="67" data-end="200"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Filling the blanks below.</span><br data-start="96" data-end="99"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Write <strong data-start="105" data-end="149">NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each question of robot below.</span></p>
<p data-start="202" data-end="338"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Ronald Fearing was required to fabricate tiny components for his robotic fly {the same way} by specialized techniques.</span></p>
<p data-start="340" data-end="481"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The robotic fly’s main structure outside is made of {carbon-fiber} and long and thin wires which make it unlike fly at all.</span></p>
<p data-start="483" data-end="621"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Cutkosky applied an artificial material in Stickybot’s {limbs | legs and feets} as a tendon to split pressure like lizard’s does.</span></p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>8. the same way<br />(Đoạn C: “Fearing has been forced to manufacture many of the other minute components of his fly in the same way, using a micromachining laser and a rapid prototyping system&#8230;”)<br />→ Ronald Fearing phải chế tạo các bộ phận siêu nhỏ the same way, tức là bằng cùng phương pháp kỹ thuật đặc biệt.<br />→ Đáp án: the same way<br /> <br />9. carbon-fiber<br />(Đoạn D: “&#8230;which contained the fly-bot itself, a delicate, origami-like framework of black carbon-fiber struts and hairlike wires that&#8230; looks nothing like a real fly.”)<br />→ Cấu trúc bên ngoài của robot làm từ carbon-fiber cùng dây mảnh như sợi tóc, khiến nó trông không giống ruồi thật.<br />→ Đáp án: carbon-fiber<br /> <br />10. limbs<br />(Đoạn F: “He subsequently embedded a branching polyester cloth ‘tendon’ in his robot’s limbs to distribute its load in the same way.”)<br />→ Cutkosky gắn “gân” nhân tạo vào limbs của Stickybot để phân bố trọng lực giống thằn lằn thật.<br />→ Đáp án: limbs<br /> <br /> <br /> </p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('816b255f-129e-4571-b666-a7bf7e3c1786', '2f6eb2ea-b58e-4749-b857-d58fe95caf75', 'fillup', 'Questions 8-13', '<p>Complete the table below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>THE DEVELOPMENT OF PAPER</strong></p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="width: 95.8146%; border-collapse: collapse; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); height: 463.625px;" border="1">
<colgroup>
<col class="ql-align-center" style="width: 28.1717%;" width="189">
<col class="ql-align-center" style="width: 15.5019%;" width="104">
<col class="ql-align-center" style="width: 28.1717%;" width="189">
<col class="ql-align-center" style="width: 28.1717%;" width="189"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 80.9688px;" data-row="1">
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="1" data-cell-bg="rgb(242, 242, 242)">
<p><strong>Place</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="1" data-cell-bg="rgb(242, 242, 242)">
<p><strong>Date of introduction</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="1" data-cell-bg="rgb(242, 242, 242)">
<p><strong>Materials used</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="1" data-cell-bg="rgb(242, 242, 242)">
<p><strong>Method of production</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 100.562px;" data-row="2">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="2" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>Egypt</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="2" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>about 2400 BC</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="2" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>a plant called papyrus</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="2" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p><span class="input-inline2 numquest">{strips} </span>of the plant weresoftened in water, woven and pounded</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 100.562px;" data-row="3">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="3" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>Europe</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="3" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>unknown</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="3" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>parchment made from the skin of animals such as { sheep}</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="3" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>skin was dried and { stretched}</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 100.562px;" data-row="4">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="4" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>China</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="4" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>105 AD</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="4" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p><span class="input-inline2 numquest">{Bark}</span> of a mulberrytree and hemp rags</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="4" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>ingredients were mixed with water, pressed and but outside in the sun</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 80.9688px;" data-row="5">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="5" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p><span class="input-inline2 numquest">{Samarkand}</span></p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="5" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>751 AD</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="5" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>flax and hemp</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="5" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">
<p>mills made of {Stone} used were</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>8. Egypt: Method of production (Papyrus)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>strips</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) &#8220;The Egyptians cut the plant into <strong>strips</strong> which they softened in water. Papyrus was cross-woven into a mat and then pounded&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cây papyrus được cắt thành các <strong>strips</strong> (dải) trước khi được xử lý tiếp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>9. Europe: Materials used (Parchment)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>sheep</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) &#8220;&#8230;it has been estimated that a single book written on parchment required the skins of 300 <strong>sheep</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Da cừu (<strong>sheep</strong>) là ví dụ cụ thể về nguyên liệu làm parchment.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>10. Europe: Method of production (Parchment)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>stretched</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) &#8220;The skins had to be specifically prepared by drying them and they were then <strong>stretched</strong> on a special frame.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Da làm parchment được làm khô và sau đó được <strong>stretched</strong> (kéo căng).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>11. China: Materials used (Paper)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Bark</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) &#8220;Ts’ai Lun seems to have made his paper by mixing finely chopped <strong>mulberry bark</strong> and hemp rags with water&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Vỏ cây (<strong>Bark</strong>) dâu tằm là một trong những nguyên liệu chính.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>12. Place: (Papermaking Center in 751 AD)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Samarkand</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) &#8220;They were taken away to <strong>Samarkand</strong>, which was a good place to make paper&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Thợ làm giấy Trung Quốc bị bắt và đưa đến <strong>Samarkand</strong>, nơi này trở thành trung tâm làm giấy.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>13. Samarkand: Method of production</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Stone</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) &#8220;Samarkanders changed the technology of manufacturing paper. They began to prepare it in <strong>stone</strong> mills&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Công nghệ mới ở Samarkand sử dụng cối xay làm bằng <strong>Stone</strong> (đá).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('53c6e7c3-200f-4275-abc4-2c44b8c91e60', '9e74c3bb-ed43-4df5-bbd1-f548be9e70f2', 'fillup', 'Questions 11–13', '<p data-start="649" data-end="787"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Fill the blanks below.</span><br data-start="675" data-end="678"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Write <strong data-start="684" data-end="728">NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer about facts of stickybot.</span></p>
<p data-start="793" data-end="917"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Stickybot’s feet doesn’t have {self-cleaning} function which makes it only be able to walk on smooth surface.</span></p>
<p data-start="923" data-end="992"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">DARPA is planning to use stickybot for {surveillance}</span></p>
<p data-start="998" data-end="1120"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Cutkosky assumes that stickybot finally has potential in {lifesaving} or other human-related activities.</span></p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>11. self-cleaning<br />(Đoạn G: “The dry adhesive on Stickybot’s toes isn’t self-cleaning like the lizard’s either, so it rapidly clogs with dirt.”)<br />→ Chất dính trên chân Stickybot không có chức năng tự làm sạch, vì vậy robot chỉ có thể di chuyển trên bề mặt trơn nhẵn.<br />→ Đáp án: self-cleaning<br /> <br />12. surveillance<br />(Đoạn G: “The Department of Defense’s Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA), which funds the project, has it in mind for surveillance: an automaton that could slink up a building and perch there for hours or days&#8230;”)<br />→ DARPA dự định sử dụng Stickybot cho mục đích surveillance (giám sát, theo dõi).<br />→ Đáp án: surveillance<br /> <br />13. lifesaving<br />(Đoạn G: “I would like to see Stickybot have a real-world function, whether it’s a toy or another application. Sure, it would be great if it eventually has a lifesaving or humanitarian role&#8230;”)<br />→ Cutkosky hy vọng Stickybot cuối cùng sẽ có vai trò lifesaving hoặc mang tính nhân đạo trong tương lai.<br />→ Đáp án: lifesaving<br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> </p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d102833b-6be8-4193-9b46-61dca0e98b07', '3d9e8e2d-6041-4585-af3b-1e7799514d54', 'radio', 'Questions 27 – 31', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "As expected, the artworks chosen for the exhibition reflect a narrow interpretation of landscape"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Academy rejected Australian suggestions for the subject of the exhibition"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The colonial relationship meant that early Australian landscape painting followed the traditions of English landscape painting"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The exhibition reflects the fact that Australian art developed its own particular qualities"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Contemporary Australian artists have generally rejected British landscape traditions"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. As expected, the artworks chosen for the exhibition reflect a narrow interpretation of landscape.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> &#8220;&#8230;this results in a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">flexible, wide-ranging notion of landscape</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định triển lãm đem lại một khái niệm về phong cảnh &#8220;linh hoạt và rộng lớn&#8221;, trái ngược với từ &#8220;narrow&#8221; (hẹp hòi) trong câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. The Academy rejected Australian suggestions for the subject of the exhibition.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến việc các chuyên gia Úc (như Mendelssohn) phê bình sự lựa chọn của Học viện, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến việc phía Úc có đưa ra đề xuất nào và bị từ chối hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. The colonial relationship meant that early Australian landscape painting followed the traditions of English landscape painting.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> &#8220;&#8230;it was <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">inevitable</strong> during Australian art’s formative years that it would <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">reflect Britain’s devotion to the beloved landscape</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Do mối quan hệ thuộc địa, nghệ thuật Úc thời kỳ đầu không thể tránh khỏi việc phản ánh sự sùng bái phong cảnh theo truyền thống của Anh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. The exhibition reflects the fact that Australian art developed its own particular qualities.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> Soriano nói: &#8220;What I wanted to show was how Australian art develops a <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">real distinctiveness</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Triển lãm nhằm mục đích cho thấy sự phát triển mang tính bản sắc riêng (distinctiveness) của nghệ thuật Úc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. Contemporary Australian artists have generally rejected British landscape traditions.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc lấy ví dụ Shaun Gladwell vẫn quan tâm đến truyền thống (Turner/Romantic landscape). Tuy nhiên, bài <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"119\">không đưa ra nhận định chung</strong> cho toàn bộ các nghệ sĩ đương đại khác là họ có &#8220;tẩy chay&#8221; truyền thống Anh hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('624b0a26-5c0b-4307-bd5f-c126245347b7', '06af1a69-1a4b-4d54-a58f-91cc45328f06', 'radio', 'Questions 36 – 40', '', '<p data-path-to-node="16,0,0">Choose<strong data-path-to-node="16,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"> TRUE</strong>: if the statement agrees with the information,<strong data-path-to-node="16,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">FALSE</strong>: if the statement contradicts the information,<strong data-path-to-node="16,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">NOT GIVEN</strong>: if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Companies usually hire people on the basis of their character."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There are some areas of sport that have a greater proportion of talent than others."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Measures of intelligence accurately predict performance at work."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There are cases in which talented sportspeople have been overlooked."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Newly formed organisations have the most highly motivated staff."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. Companies usually hire people on the basis of their character. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Most recruitment decisions are influenced by the <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">skills and abilities</strong> of an individual rather than their <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">aptitude and attitude</strong>.” (Đoạn A)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói các công ty thuê dựa trên kỹ năng/khả năng chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">không phải</strong> thái độ/tính cách (aptitude/attitude/character). Thông tin mâu thuẫn nên chọn <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. There are some areas of sport that have a greater proportion of talent than others. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến thể thao (bóng rổ, bóng bầu dục) để làm ví dụ về việc đánh giá sai tài năng, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">không hề so sánh</strong> tỷ lệ tài năng giữa các môn thể thao với nhau.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Measures of intelligence accurately predict performance at work. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…research shows that the best predictors… tend to be measures of intelligence. <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">But even these measures correlate only loosely with performance</strong>…” (Đoạn D)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói các thước đo trí tuệ chỉ liên quan <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">lỏng lẻo</strong> (loosely) chứ không phải <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">chính xác</strong> (accurately). Do đó câu này mâu thuẫn. (Lưu ý đáp án bạn đưa ra là T nhưng dẫn chứng bài học cho thấy nó phải là F).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. There are cases in which talented sportspeople have been overlooked. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Basketball star <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">Michael Jordan was dropped</strong> by his high-school basketball coach and a number of top American football quarterbacks were available early in their careers because they were <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"198\">not considered good enough</strong>…” (Đoạn D)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Michael Jordan từng bị loại, điều này chứng minh các vận động viên tài năng từng bị bỏ qua/đánh giá thấp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. Newly formed organisations have the most highly motivated staff. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc không có thông tin về “tổ chức mới thành lập” (<em data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">newly formed organisations</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7c5d401d-c6c2-4103-b0c3-abf88d14453c', 'fc58de3b-7259-42f9-b8cc-524861f0eec8', 'matching', 'Questions 14-20', NULL, '<p>Reading passage has seven paragraphs,<strong> A–G</strong></p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of heading below.</p>
<p>Write the correct number, i-viii, in boxes 14-20 on your answer sheet.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i How CSR may help one business to expand"}, {"optionText": "ii CSR in many aspects of a company’s business"}, {"optionText": "iii A CSR initiative without a financial gain"}, {"optionText": "iv Lack of action by the state of social issues"}, {"optionText": "v Drives or pressures motivate companies to address CSR"}, {"optionText": "vi The past illustrates business are responsible for future outcomes"}, {"optionText": "vii Companies applying CSR should be selective"}, {"optionText": "viii Reasons that business and society benefit each other"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<h4 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đoạn A: {v Drives or pressures motivate companies to address CSR}</strong></h4>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Nowadays, <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">governments and companies need to account for</strong> the social consequences of their actions… CSR has become a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">priority for business leaders</strong>… every company needs <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"182\">tacit or explicit permission</strong> from governments…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này thảo luận về các động lực (drives) như nghĩa vụ đạo đức, sự bền vững và áp lực (pressures) từ chính phủ/cộng đồng (giấy phép hoạt động) khiến các nhà lãnh đạo phải ưu tiên CSR.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đoạn B: {viii Reasons that business and society benefit each other}</strong></h4>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Successful corporations need a healthy society</strong>… At the same time, <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">a healthy society needs successful companies</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả liệt kê hàng loạt lý do: Xã hội khỏe mạnh cung cấp lao động năng suất và khách hàng; ngược lại, doanh nghiệp tạo ra việc làm, sự giàu có và đổi mới. Đây là mối quan hệ tương hỗ (benefit each other).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đoạn C: {vi The past illustrates business are responsible for future outcomes}</strong></h4>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Asbestos</strong>, now understood as a serious health risk was thought to be safe in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">early 1900s</strong>… firms that failed to anticipated the consequences… have been <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">bankrupted</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ví dụ về Amiăng (asbestos) trong quá khứ cho thấy nếu doanh nghiệp không dự đoán được tác động xã hội trong tương lai, họ sẽ phải trả giá đắt (phá sản).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đoạn D: {vii Companies applying CSR should be selective}</strong></h4>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “No business can solve all of society’s problems… Instead, each company <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">must select issues that intersect with its particular business</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định doanh nghiệp không nên làm CSR tràn lan mà phải có tính <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">chọn lọc (selective)</strong>, tập trung vào những vấn đề liên quan trực tiếp đến ngành nghề của mình.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đoạn E: {iii A CSR initiative without a financial gain}</strong></h4>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “No matter how beneficial the program is, it remains <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">incidental to the company’s business</strong>, and the <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">direct effect on GE’s recruiting and retention is modest</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ví dụ về General Electronics (GE) hỗ trợ trường học. Dù chương trình rất tốt về mặt xã hội, nhưng nó không liên quan trực tiếp đến hoạt động kinh doanh cốt lõi của GE và mang lại lợi ích tài chính/nhân sự rất ít (incidental/modest).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đoạn F: {i How CSR may help one business to expand}</strong></h4>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">shortage of information technology workers</strong> is a significant <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">constraint on Microsoft’s growth</strong>… Microsoft’s $50 million initiative was aimed at… having a <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"172\">direct-and potentially significant-impact on the company</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Microsoft đầu tư vào các trường cao đẳng cộng đồng để đào tạo nhân lực IT. Việc này giúp giải quyết sự thiếu hụt nhân lực, từ đó giúp công ty mở rộng (expand) và tăng trưởng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đoạn G: {ii CSR in many aspects of a company’s business}</strong></h4>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “In short, <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">nearly every aspect of the company’s value chain</strong> reinforces the social dimensions… sourcing… stores construction… renewable wind energy… biofuels… cleaning products…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ví dụ về Whole Foods Market cho thấy CSR thấm đẫm trong <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">mọi khía cạnh</strong> (many aspects) của doanh nghiệp, từ thu mua, xây dựng cửa hàng, năng lượng đến vệ sinh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('307d3986-6d46-46f5-81d9-0f195d663a70', 'fc58de3b-7259-42f9-b8cc-524861f0eec8', 'fillup', 'Questions 21-22', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the passage of each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 21-22 on your answer sheet</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>The implement of CSR, HOW?</strong></span></p>
<p>Promotion of CSR requires the understanding of interdependence between business and society. Corporations workers’ productivity generally needs healthcare, education, and given {equal opportunity} Restrictions imposed by government and companies both protect consumers from being treated unfairly. Improvement ofthe safety standard can reduce the {internal costs} of accidents in the workplace. Similarly society becomes a pool of more human needs and aspirations</p>
', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong>21. Corporations workers’ productivity generally needs healthcare, education, and given <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> equal opportunity.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>equal opportunity</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “Education, health care, and <strong>equal opportunity</strong> are essential lo a productive workforce.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong>22. Improvement of the safety standard can reduce the <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> costs of accidents in the workplace.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>internal costs</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “Safe products and working conditions not only attract customers but lower the <strong>internal costs</strong> of accidents.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\">(Lưu ý: Đáp án “internal costs” là chính xác nhất theo văn bản. Tuy nhiên, nếu chỉ được dùng 2 từ, “costs of accidents” cũng là một khả năng. Dựa trên câu hỏi, “internal costs” là cụm 2 từ có ý nghĩa hoàn chỉnh.)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8ff98aff-90c1-4121-8e00-ec5380da6378', 'fc58de3b-7259-42f9-b8cc-524861f0eec8', 'matrix', 'Questions 23-26', NULL, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Look at the following opinions or deeds (Questions 23-26) and the list of companies below.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Match each opinion or deed with the correct company, A, B or C.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Write the correct letter, A, B or C in boxes 23-26 on your answer sheet.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">NB You may use any letter more than once</span></p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The disposable waste", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "The way company purchases as goods", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Helping the undeveloped", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Ensuring the people have the latest information", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "General Electronics", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Microsoft", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Whole Foods Market", "categoryLetter": "C"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>23. The disposable waste</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: C</strong> (Whole Foods Market)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “<strong>Spoiled produce and biodegradable waste</strong> are trucked to regional centers for <strong>composting</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Whole Foods xử lý chất thải hữu cơ và sản phẩm hỏng (disposable waste) bằng cách ủ phân (composting).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>24. The way company purchases as goods</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: C</strong> (Whole Foods Market)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “The company’s <strong>sourcing emphasises purchases from local farmers</strong> through each store’s procurement process. Buyers screen out foods containing any of nearly 100 common ingredients…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Whole Foods có quy trình tìm nguồn cung ứng (<strong>purchases as goods</strong> / sourcing) rất cụ thể, nhấn mạnh sản phẩm hữu cơ và địa phương.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>25. Helping the undeveloped</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: A</strong> (General Electronics)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “A good example is General Electronics’s program to <strong>adopt under-performing public high schools</strong> near several of its major U.S. facilities.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> GE hỗ trợ các trường học hoạt động kém (under-performing/undeveloped) bằng tài chính, sản phẩm và cố vấn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>26. Ensuring the people have the latest information</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: B</strong> (Microsoft)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “Microsoft recognizes, however, that community colleges face special challenges: IT curricula are not standardized, technology used in classrooms is often outdated, and there are no systematic <strong>professional development programs to keep faculty up to date</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Microsoft giải quyết vấn đề tài liệu lỗi thời và thiếu các chương trình phát triển chuyên môn để giữ cho giảng viên “up to date” (có thông tin mới nhất).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
SET session_replication_role = DEFAULT;
